12/11/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government decided Monday (11 November) that Macedonia will require an international military presence after NATO's Amber Fox mission expires on 15 December.
Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski says that the foreign and defence ministries, in co-operation with representatives of the international community, will define the mandate, size and objectives of the new mission.
In other news, Dutch Foreign Minister Jaap de Hoop Scheffer visited Skopje on Monday and held a series of meetings with officials, including counterpart Ilinka Mitreva, President Boris Trajkovski, and new Prime Minister Branco Crvenkovski.Dutch participation in Amber Fox was among the topics discussed.
(MIA - 12/11/02;
BBC Monitoring, Makfax - 11/11/02)
